26/01/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- A multinational seven-day exercise involving NATO member states and nine partner countries kicks off Wednesday (26 January) in the partners' capitals.
The annual event is aimed at improving crisis management capacities.
Among Southeast European countries, the exercise includes NATO members Bulgaria, Greece, Romania and Turkey, as well as two partner nations -- Croatia and Macedonia.
In other news, the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- wrapped up a two-day meeting in Zagreb on Tuesday, announcing that they would deploy a joint medical team in Afghanistan in August.
The agreement was reached with input from the United States.
(bTV, BNR, Vecernji list - 26/01/05;
NATO Web site, HINA, Macedonian government Web site - 19/01/05)
